<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="section section-light">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">Do I need a GP referral? No — book directly</button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>No GP referral is needed for osteopathy appointments. You can book directly online or by calling us. If you have an ACC claim, we can process it for you at your first visit.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">How many sessions will I need</button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>This varies depending on your condition. Many patients notice improvement after 1-3 sessions. During your first consultation, we'll discuss a treatment plan tailored to your needs.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">What should I wear to my appointment</button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Wear comfortable, loose-fitting clothing that allows easy movement. We may need to examine and treat areas around your complaint, so clothing you can move easily in is ideal.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">What's the difference between osteopathy and physiotherapy?</button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>While both professions treat musculoskeletal conditions, osteopathy takes a whole-body approach, looking at how all systems interconnect. Osteopaths use a wider range of hands-on techniques including joint mobilisation, soft tissue work, and cranial techniques.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
